<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="878" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d878">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.6200/41a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Swiss Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RDP1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Ritter</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 346</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-13">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that
                                telegrams have been received from the consular representatives of
                                this Government at numerous cities abroad reporting that there are
                                no Swiss consuls at those places to whom German interests can be
                                turned over. For example, I am advised that there are no Swiss
                                consular officers at Barbados, Cairo, Martinique, Hongkong, Azores,
                                Lourenço Marques, and Port of Spain.</p>
                            <p>I should be greatly pleased if you will ascertain by telegraph the
                                wishes of the German Government as to what disposition it desires to
                                have made of its interests at such places where there are no Swiss
                                consular officers.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>